Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper discusses the use of ground-based sky cameras for analyzing cloud properties, which involves image processing and analysis. This makes cs.CV the most likely sub-category. 
2. cs.GR (Graphics): The paper involves the analysis of images captured by sky cameras, which could fall under the sub-category of graphics. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper could also fall under the sub-category of AI, as it involves the use of machine learning algorithms for cloud analysis. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper could also fall under the sub-category of IR, as it involves the retrieval of information from images captured by sky cameras. 
5. cs.SD (Software Development): The paper could also fall under the sub-category of SD, as it involves the development of software for cloud analysis using ground-based sky cameras.
